WEBVTT

00:01.633 --> 00:03.633
♪♪♪

00:06.933 --> 00:08.200
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:08.267 --> 00:10.233
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:10.300 --> 00:11.467
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:11.533 --> 00:12.467
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:12.533 --> 00:13.600
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:13.667 --> 00:14.800
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:14.867 --> 00:16.733
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:16.800 --> 00:18.467
♪ Ben 10! ♪

00:27.300 --> 00:29.267
Ben: [ Groans ]

00:29.333 --> 00:32.367
It's so hot.

00:32.433 --> 00:33.694
Get off the sidewalk, Ben.

00:33.718 --> 00:35.000
No.

00:35.067 --> 00:36.577
The sun has claimed

00:36.601 --> 00:38.133
another victim.

00:38.200 --> 00:39.700
Goodbye.

00:39.767 --> 00:41.677
- [ Grunts ] - There.

00:41.767 --> 00:43.976
- It's like a bajillion degrees - hotter on the sidewalk.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.127
[ Groans ]

00:45.151 --> 00:46.300
You may have a point.

00:46.367 --> 00:47.527
Okay, kids.

00:47.551 --> 00:48.733
Ready to walk around?

00:48.800 --> 00:50.310
- Uh, Ben, - what are you doing?

00:50.400 --> 00:51.377
He's fine, Grandpa.

00:51.401 --> 00:52.401
[ Grunts ]

00:52.467 --> 00:53.700
[ Groans ]

00:53.767 --> 00:55.376
- Why are we even standing outside - right now?

00:55.400 --> 00:57.044
- Just take a look around, - Ben.

00:57.133 --> 00:58.777
You can't find a vista like this

00:58.801 --> 01:00.467
anywhere else in the world.

01:00.533 --> 01:02.667
It's just a pile of rocks!

01:02.733 --> 01:03.894
Well, it's truly

01:03.918 --> 01:05.100
a masterpiece of nature.

01:05.167 --> 01:06.394
Sure, it goes hand in hand

01:06.418 --> 01:07.667
with this outrageous heat.

01:07.733 --> 01:09.643
- Sometimes you just have to - put up with the bad

01:09.667 --> 01:10.967
To appreciate the good.

01:11.033 --> 01:12.377
Hey, Ben!

01:12.401 --> 01:13.767
I bet these will keep you cool.

01:13.833 --> 01:14.994
By connecting

01:15.018 --> 01:16.200
with these crystals,

01:16.267 --> 01:18.944
I'll be able to communicate

01:18.968 --> 01:21.667
with nature and beat the heat.

01:21.733 --> 01:23.300
Where'd you figure that out?

01:23.367 --> 01:24.733
It says so in this pamphlet.

01:24.800 --> 01:26.044
♪ <i>How to connect</i>

01:26.068 --> 01:27.333
<i>with your crystals ♪</i>

01:27.400 --> 01:29.100
Mud slide!

01:29.167 --> 01:31.867
[ People screaming ]

01:31.933 --> 01:33.276
- It's heading - straight for the town!

01:33.300 --> 01:34.827
Don't worry, guys.

01:34.851 --> 01:36.400
Heatblast's got this.

01:36.467 --> 01:39.667
♪♪♪

01:46.300 --> 01:47.567
Four Arms?

01:47.633 --> 01:49.100
Plus more?

01:49.167 --> 01:50.733
This is no problem.

01:50.800 --> 01:53.267
I just got to dig a ditch.

01:53.333 --> 01:54.367
Huh?

01:54.433 --> 01:56.600
[ Electricity crackles ]

01:59.200 --> 02:01.033
Nice job, blue hands.

02:01.100 --> 02:02.767
"Thank you."

02:06.133 --> 02:09.267
Hang tight!

02:09.333 --> 02:10.600
[ Both gasp ]

02:10.667 --> 02:12.833
Is this a performance piece?

02:12.900 --> 02:15.094
I love performance pieces.

02:15.118 --> 02:17.333
So moving.

02:17.400 --> 02:18.433
Hmm.

02:18.500 --> 02:19.694
Gee, Ben, that was...

02:19.718 --> 02:20.933
Weird.

02:21.000 --> 02:23.494
I know! But, I mean, I did save

02:23.518 --> 02:26.033
the town, so crisis averted.

02:26.100 --> 02:27.267
I don't know, Ben.

02:27.333 --> 02:28.394
These plasma powers

02:28.418 --> 02:29.500
are kind of unpredictable.

02:29.567 --> 02:30.943
- Are you sure - you can handle this?

02:30.967 --> 02:32.377
Yeah, no problem.

02:32.401 --> 02:33.833
Besides, that wasn't me.

02:33.900 --> 02:35.044
It was...

02:35.068 --> 02:36.233
Vilgax: The Omnitrix!

02:38.467 --> 02:39.600
Vilgax!

02:39.667 --> 02:40.877
Heed my warning,

02:40.901 --> 02:42.133
Earth child.

02:42.200 --> 02:44.244
That device

02:44.268 --> 02:46.333
will be your undoing.

02:46.400 --> 02:48.033
The only undoing

02:48.100 --> 02:50.077
will be your face

02:50.101 --> 02:52.100
against my fist!

02:52.167 --> 02:53.667
[ Grunts ]

02:53.733 --> 02:55.427
This performance piece

02:55.451 --> 02:57.167
is too moving!

02:57.233 --> 02:58.900
Huh? What was that?

02:58.967 --> 03:01.900
A display of untamed power.

03:01.967 --> 03:03.700
I'm not here to squabble.

03:03.767 --> 03:05.794
Me neither, 'cause

03:05.818 --> 03:07.867
I'm about to send you packing.

03:07.933 --> 03:09.677
- Aaaa... - [ Beeping ]

03:09.767 --> 03:10.677
- aah! - [ Grunts ]

03:10.767 --> 03:12.300
[ Gasps ]

03:12.367 --> 03:14.433
Wait, wait.

03:14.500 --> 03:15.433
What?

03:15.500 --> 03:17.000
Both: Ben!

03:17.067 --> 03:18.000
Are you okay?

03:18.067 --> 03:18.833
I don't know.

03:18.900 --> 03:20.011
We have our differences,

03:20.035 --> 03:21.167
boy,

03:21.233 --> 03:22.960
and there will come a reckoning,

03:22.984 --> 03:24.733
but not today.

03:24.800 --> 03:25.977
Today,

03:26.001 --> 03:27.200
I come not for battle,

03:27.267 --> 03:28.877
but to protect you

03:28.901 --> 03:30.533
from the Omnitrix.

03:30.600 --> 03:32.133
What are you talking about?

03:32.200 --> 03:34.161
Your talent to harness

03:34.185 --> 03:36.167
the DNA is admirable,

03:36.233 --> 03:37.727
but the Omnitrix

03:37.751 --> 03:39.267
was never meant for humans,

03:39.333 --> 03:41.100
especially not a child.

03:41.167 --> 03:42.561
Child?

03:42.585 --> 03:44.000
Double digits, ugly.

03:44.067 --> 03:45.327
Look at what your powers

03:45.351 --> 03:46.633
have wrought.

03:46.700 --> 03:48.600
Soon the Omnitrix energies

03:48.667 --> 03:50.061
will become too much

03:50.085 --> 03:51.500
for you to handle.

03:51.567 --> 03:53.844
The biggest threat

03:53.868 --> 03:56.167
to your beloved planet is you.

03:56.233 --> 03:57.577
That's bogus!

03:57.601 --> 03:58.967
He's clearly lying.

03:59.033 --> 04:01.209
- He's just trying to trick you - into giving him the Omnitrix.

04:01.233 --> 04:03.260
Yeah, you're right,

04:03.284 --> 04:05.333
and I'm gonna prove it.

04:07.200 --> 04:08.761
You wanted it?

04:08.785 --> 04:10.367
You got it.

04:14.167 --> 04:15.900
Huh? Snow?

04:15.967 --> 04:17.644
Huh, what?

04:17.668 --> 04:19.367
Did I do this?

04:19.433 --> 04:21.000
[ Muffled screams ]

04:21.067 --> 04:23.027
Oh! Whoa!

04:23.051 --> 04:25.033
No, no, no!

04:25.100 --> 04:26.233
I'm sorry.

04:26.300 --> 04:28.033
Uh, Ben!

04:28.100 --> 04:29.161
Uh, don't worry,

04:29.185 --> 04:30.267
I'll get you out.

04:30.333 --> 04:31.844
Stop!

04:31.868 --> 04:33.400
You've done enough damage here,

04:33.467 --> 04:36.600
Ben, destroyer of ships.

04:36.667 --> 04:38.333
You destroy one ship,

04:38.400 --> 04:40.127
and suddenly you're

04:38.400 --> 04:41.900
[ Beeping ]

04:40.151 --> 04:41.967
the destroyer of ships.

04:41.967 --> 04:43.700
[ Chuckles nervously ]

04:43.767 --> 04:45.167
[ Grunts ]

04:45.233 --> 04:47.167
No! Huh?

04:48.767 --> 04:52.433
[ Shivering ] So moving.

04:54.600 --> 04:55.833
You guys okay?

04:55.900 --> 04:57.027
[ Shivering ] W-W-We're...

04:57.051 --> 04:58.200
We're c-c-cool.

04:58.267 --> 04:59.267
[ Chuckles ]

04:59.300 --> 05:00.511
[ Shivering ] Ice one,

05:00.535 --> 05:01.767
G-G-Grandpa.

05:01.833 --> 05:03.177
You see, child,

05:03.201 --> 05:04.567
this is proof enough

05:04.633 --> 05:05.844
that you can't handle

05:05.868 --> 05:07.100
these powers.

05:07.167 --> 05:08.211
The very elements

05:08.235 --> 05:09.300
are against you.

05:09.367 --> 05:10.377
If you want

05:10.401 --> 05:11.433
to save the Earth,

05:11.500 --> 05:13.111
give me the Omnitrix

05:13.135 --> 05:14.767
and I'll leave this planet.

05:14.833 --> 05:16.400
Can you believe this guy?

05:16.467 --> 05:17.994
Trying to tell <i>me</i>

05:18.018 --> 05:19.567
how the Omnitrix works.

05:19.633 --> 05:22.033
What a joke, right, guys?

05:22.100 --> 05:23.333
Guys?

05:23.400 --> 05:24.733
Ben, I trust you,

05:24.800 --> 05:26.577
and the last thing we want to do

05:26.601 --> 05:28.400
is give the Omnitrix to Vilgax.

05:28.467 --> 05:29.733
But you've got to admit,

05:29.800 --> 05:31.227
the Omnitrix has been doing

05:31.251 --> 05:32.700
weird things lately.

05:33.800 --> 05:35.011
Like that.

05:35.035 --> 05:36.267
A new guy?

05:36.333 --> 05:37.567
Whoa! Aah!

05:37.633 --> 05:38.810
Do not activate

05:38.834 --> 05:40.033
that alien!

05:40.100 --> 05:42.067
It will tear you apart,

05:42.133 --> 05:43.544
and the rest of the world

05:43.568 --> 05:45.000
along with it.

05:45.067 --> 05:47.327
Only one way to find out,

05:47.351 --> 05:49.633
Mr. Suddenly Sensitive Bad Guy.

05:49.700 --> 05:51.533
No!

05:51.600 --> 05:54.800
♪♪♪

06:06.433 --> 06:07.700
[ Gasps ]

06:07.767 --> 06:09.227
You have no idea

06:09.251 --> 06:10.733
what you've just done.

06:10.800 --> 06:12.277
Ha! I know exactly

06:12.301 --> 06:13.800
what I've done.

06:13.867 --> 06:15.111
He's made entirely

06:15.135 --> 06:16.400
of that blue energy stuff.

06:16.467 --> 06:18.600
Yeah, you're ri... Aah!

06:18.667 --> 06:20.067
Both: Ben!

06:20.133 --> 06:21.577
[ Groans ]

06:20.133 --> 06:23.067
to battle,

06:21.601 --> 06:23.133
I did not come here

06:23.133 --> 06:25.067
but you leave me no choice.

06:25.133 --> 06:27.900
This alien must be subdued.

06:27.967 --> 06:28.994
What's so special

06:29.018 --> 06:30.067
about this alien, huh?

06:30.133 --> 06:31.400
It will destroy you

06:31.467 --> 06:32.877
and every other living thing

06:32.901 --> 06:34.333
on this planet,

06:34.400 --> 06:36.100
including me!

06:38.733 --> 06:41.400
Whoa!

06:41.467 --> 06:43.011
The only chance you have

06:43.035 --> 06:44.600
to save your world

06:44.667 --> 06:45.677
is to surrender

06:45.701 --> 06:46.733
the Omnitrix.

06:46.800 --> 06:47.944
[ Grunting ]

06:47.968 --> 06:49.133
Aah!

06:49.200 --> 06:50.277
You're not getting

06:50.301 --> 06:51.400
this watch.

06:51.467 --> 06:53.094
I thought you cared

06:53.118 --> 06:54.767
for this planet,

06:54.833 --> 06:57.133
but apparently you do not!

06:57.200 --> 06:58.867
No!

07:00.400 --> 07:02.233
Whoa.

07:04.833 --> 07:07.367
Aah!

07:07.433 --> 07:08.500
Whoa.

07:08.567 --> 07:10.367
♪♪♪

07:10.433 --> 07:12.694
You care more about playing

07:12.718 --> 07:15.000
the hero than saving the Earth.

07:15.067 --> 07:17.533
I fear for us all.

07:20.033 --> 07:23.200
[ Thunder crashing ]

07:26.967 --> 07:28.127
These should dry pretty fast

07:28.151 --> 07:29.333
in this heat.

07:29.400 --> 07:31.011
Yeah, but I bet they would dry

07:31.035 --> 07:32.667
five times faster

07:32.733 --> 07:34.000
if we had Heatblast.

07:34.067 --> 07:35.200
Right, Ben?

07:35.267 --> 07:36.633
Ben?

07:36.700 --> 07:38.767
♪♪♪

07:38.833 --> 07:40.310
- -Huh? - -Hey.

07:40.400 --> 07:42.733
Ugh. I'm brooding.

07:42.800 --> 07:44.510
- What makes this - so brood-worthy?

07:44.600 --> 07:46.233
It's just all a big mess.

07:46.300 --> 07:47.676
- If I give the Omnitrix - to Vilgax,

07:47.700 --> 07:49.167
He'll take over the world.

07:49.233 --> 07:51.010
If I keep using this new alien,

07:51.034 --> 07:52.833
I might destroy the world.

07:52.900 --> 07:54.133
But worst of all,

07:54.200 --> 07:55.744
I could stop being a hero

07:55.768 --> 07:57.333
and just become old.

07:57.400 --> 07:59.261
And then I never used

07:59.285 --> 08:01.167
the Omnitrix ever again.

08:01.233 --> 08:02.444
[ Children booing ]

08:02.468 --> 08:03.700
No! Aah! My heart!

08:03.767 --> 08:06.867
My life is over!

08:06.933 --> 08:08.044
Aw, come on.

08:08.068 --> 08:09.200
Unh-unh.

08:09.267 --> 08:11.010
- You just need - some guidance.

08:11.100 --> 08:12.311
Perhaps

08:12.335 --> 08:13.567
of the crystal variety?

08:13.633 --> 08:15.000
Ow! Cut it out!

08:15.067 --> 08:16.843
- You've been through - a lot worse than this.

08:16.867 --> 08:18.176
- You'll figure out - how to fix it.

08:18.200 --> 08:20.033
What would Grandpa say?

08:20.100 --> 08:21.711
Both: Tennysons don't run away

08:21.735 --> 08:23.367
from their fears.

08:23.433 --> 08:24.533
We face them.

08:24.600 --> 08:25.800
[ Both laugh ]

08:25.867 --> 08:27.133
You're right.

08:27.200 --> 08:28.743
- I just need some space - to figure this thing out.

08:28.767 --> 08:30.311
The desert's a perfect place

08:30.335 --> 08:31.900
to get all introspective.

08:31.967 --> 08:34.061
Ah, yes. What a nice,

08:34.085 --> 08:36.200
quiet space for thinking.

08:36.267 --> 08:37.511
Bah!

08:36.267 --> 08:38.800
all these people here?

08:37.535 --> 08:38.867
Why are

08:38.867 --> 08:40.477
- Tevin: - We're all spirit walking.

08:40.567 --> 08:42.327
I'm walking to discover the

08:42.351 --> 08:44.133
true meaning of my existence.

08:44.200 --> 08:45.233
Uh...

08:45.300 --> 08:46.800
Aha!

08:46.867 --> 08:48.577
- I can try out my alien - here.

08:48.667 --> 08:50.444
- No people, - no buildings.

08:50.533 --> 08:52.400
Let's do this.

08:52.467 --> 08:54.267
[ Inhales ]

08:54.333 --> 08:58.000
[ Electricity crackles ]

08:58.067 --> 08:59.161
Cool, cool.

08:59.185 --> 09:00.300
Harmless so far.

09:00.367 --> 09:01.561
Okay then.

09:01.585 --> 09:02.800
Let's go bigger.

09:02.867 --> 09:05.267
[ Grunts ]

09:05.333 --> 09:06.833
Ooh.

09:06.900 --> 09:08.067
It's a sign!

09:08.133 --> 09:09.533
[ Laughs ] Yeah!

09:09.600 --> 09:11.433
That's pretty cool, huh?

09:11.500 --> 09:13.400
So far, so good.

09:13.467 --> 09:15.744
- This is probably - just a coincidence, huh, Ben?

09:15.833 --> 09:17.400
Uh, yeah.

09:17.467 --> 09:19.177
- A little rain - never hurt anyone,

09:19.267 --> 09:22.094
And it's definitely not gonna

09:22.118 --> 09:24.967
stop me from trying this!

09:25.033 --> 09:26.867
Is that a blue boomerang?

09:26.933 --> 09:28.844
Blue bluemerang!

09:28.868 --> 09:30.800
[ Laughs ]

09:30.867 --> 09:33.500
Go, go bluemerang!

09:33.567 --> 09:35.500
♪♪♪

09:35.567 --> 09:36.467
Now come back.

09:36.533 --> 09:38.344
- Huh, I think the rain - is stopping.

09:38.433 --> 09:39.510
That's got to be

09:39.534 --> 09:40.633
a good sign.

09:40.700 --> 09:42.344
Okay, this one

09:42.368 --> 09:44.033
is <i>not</i> a coincidence.

09:44.100 --> 09:45.544
It doesn't just casually snow

09:45.568 --> 09:47.033
in the desert.

09:47.100 --> 09:48.077
[ Grunts ]

09:48.101 --> 09:49.101
I hate this.

09:49.167 --> 09:50.777
- I don't know - what I'm doing wrong.

09:50.867 --> 09:52.533
[ Grunts ]

09:53.733 --> 09:54.667
Both: Huh?

09:54.733 --> 09:56.800
♪♪♪

09:56.867 --> 09:58.310
- Uh... - [ Chuckles ]

09:58.400 --> 10:00.410
- Well, at least - this is more like the desert.

10:00.500 --> 10:02.127
[ Groans ]

10:02.151 --> 10:03.800
This is going nowhere.

10:03.867 --> 10:05.361
I got to figure this out before

10:05.385 --> 10:06.900
I do something really bad.

10:06.967 --> 10:08.667
I can control this.

10:08.733 --> 10:11.733
[ Grunting ]

10:17.867 --> 10:18.927
No blizzard,

10:18.951 --> 10:20.033
no heat flash.

10:20.100 --> 10:22.000
I think we're fine.

10:22.067 --> 10:23.267
Yeah.

10:23.333 --> 10:24.377
Oh, yeah.

10:24.401 --> 10:25.467
Take that, Vilgax!

10:25.533 --> 10:26.860
Ooh, ooh!

10:26.884 --> 10:28.233
This hero can handle anything.

10:28.300 --> 10:29.700
Yeah!

10:29.767 --> 10:31.233
[ Wind howling ]

10:31.300 --> 10:32.967
Huh?

10:35.933 --> 10:37.044
Oh, no!

10:37.068 --> 10:38.200
The spirit walkers!

10:38.267 --> 10:39.494
Well, if I made it,

10:39.518 --> 10:40.767
I can stop it, right?

10:40.833 --> 10:44.167
Stop! Stop!

10:44.233 --> 10:46.400
We should run.

10:46.467 --> 10:48.700
Aah!

10:48.767 --> 10:49.867
Gwen!

10:49.933 --> 10:53.667
[ Grunting ]

10:56.733 --> 10:59.000
AAh!

10:59.067 --> 11:01.067
Aah!

11:02.167 --> 11:05.433
♪♪♪

11:07.500 --> 11:10.333
Aah!

11:10.400 --> 11:11.533
[ People screaming ]

11:11.600 --> 11:14.467
Stupid watch, stupid powers!

11:14.533 --> 11:15.710
- [ Beeping ] - Huh?

11:15.800 --> 11:17.644
What? Does it have feelings...

11:17.668 --> 11:19.533
Now!

11:19.600 --> 11:21.133
[ Screaming ]

11:21.200 --> 11:22.744
No!

11:22.768 --> 11:24.333
Stinkfly, come on!

11:24.400 --> 11:27.867
♪♪♪

11:41.733 --> 11:43.467
Here we go!

11:43.533 --> 11:45.760
It's not Stinkfly, but bigger

11:45.784 --> 11:48.033
guns means more Overflow!

11:49.700 --> 11:51.567
[ People screaming ]

11:54.900 --> 11:57.033
[ Gasps ] Aah!

11:58.767 --> 12:01.067
[ Gasps ]

12:01.133 --> 12:02.960
That was a close one.

12:02.984 --> 12:04.833
Yep, closest.

12:04.900 --> 12:06.067
Are you okay?

12:06.133 --> 12:07.809
- A little dirty water - never hurt anyone,

12:07.833 --> 12:08.810
Especially considering

12:08.834 --> 12:09.834
the alternative.

12:09.900 --> 12:11.644
Yeah, let's go back

12:11.668 --> 12:13.433
to the Rust Bucket.

12:13.500 --> 12:15.294
Max: Leave them over the fire

12:15.318 --> 12:17.133
too long and you get burnt goo.

12:17.200 --> 12:18.567
Take it away too early,

12:18.633 --> 12:20.209
- and you might as well eat them - out of the bag.

12:20.233 --> 12:22.333
It's about balance, kids.

12:22.400 --> 12:23.333
Ahh, there.

12:23.400 --> 12:24.511
The perfect roasted

12:24.535 --> 12:25.667
marshmallows.

12:25.733 --> 12:26.844
- [ Squawks ] - [ Sighs ]

12:26.933 --> 12:27.910
Well,

12:27.934 --> 12:28.934
I guess I'm going to bed.

12:29.000 --> 12:30.027
Don't stay up too late.

12:30.051 --> 12:31.100
Goodnight, Grandpa.

12:31.167 --> 12:32.511
You know, I don't think birds

12:32.535 --> 12:33.900
eat marshmallows.

12:33.967 --> 12:36.033
Gwen, what am I good at?

12:36.100 --> 12:37.077
Well, you're definitely

12:37.101 --> 12:38.101
not good at mini golf.

12:38.167 --> 12:39.777
- But you're great - at being a hero.

12:39.867 --> 12:41.111
[ Groans ]

12:41.135 --> 12:42.400
But what if Vilgax was right?

12:42.467 --> 12:43.794
What are you talking about?

12:43.818 --> 12:45.167
You saved everyone today.

12:45.233 --> 12:46.767
I saved them from me.

12:46.833 --> 12:47.944
My new alien

12:47.968 --> 12:49.100
caused that tornado.

12:49.167 --> 12:50.594
What happens if I end up really

12:50.618 --> 12:52.067
hurting someone next time?

12:52.133 --> 12:54.077
- What if I hurt you - or Grandpa?

12:54.167 --> 12:56.044
I think maybe I really do need

12:56.068 --> 12:57.967
to give up the watch.

12:58.033 --> 12:59.933
You know what you need?

13:00.000 --> 13:01.967
Self-reflective energies!

13:02.033 --> 13:03.810
- [ Sighs ] - Not this again.

13:03.900 --> 13:06.000
Ooh.

13:06.067 --> 13:07.233
Stop doing that!

13:07.300 --> 13:08.300
Nope.

13:08.367 --> 13:09.511
I know things

13:09.535 --> 13:10.700
didn't go great last time,

13:10.767 --> 13:11.843
but you can't just give up.

13:11.867 --> 13:13.233
Maybe these will help.

13:13.300 --> 13:15.376
- The pamphlet says - when you look into the crystals,

13:15.400 --> 13:17.440
- You can find all the answers - you're looking for.

13:17.467 --> 13:18.561
[ Sighs ]

13:18.585 --> 13:19.700
I'm going for a walk.

13:19.767 --> 13:21.067
See? You're doing it.

13:21.133 --> 13:22.833
I'm just taking a walk.

13:22.900 --> 13:24.200
Tell it to the crystals!

13:24.267 --> 13:25.933
You'll make the right choice.

13:26.000 --> 13:28.533
[ Chanting ]

13:28.600 --> 13:30.394
All right, crystals, you don't

13:30.418 --> 13:32.233
like me and I don't like you,

13:32.300 --> 13:34.144
- but we got to work together - here.

13:34.233 --> 13:35.277
Whoa!

13:35.301 --> 13:36.367
That's a huge crystal.

13:36.433 --> 13:37.694
Of course

13:37.718 --> 13:39.000
it's a big crystal.

13:39.067 --> 13:40.733
Ugh, you guys again?

13:40.800 --> 13:42.261
Big problems

13:42.285 --> 13:43.767
require big crystals.

13:43.833 --> 13:45.000
Now hush.

13:45.067 --> 13:46.344
Tevin's trying

13:46.368 --> 13:47.667
to have an epiphany.

13:47.733 --> 13:48.844
Tevin: <i>You</i> were trying

13:48.868 --> 13:50.000
to have an epiphany.

13:50.067 --> 13:51.477
Hmm.

13:51.501 --> 13:52.933
Big problems...

13:53.000 --> 13:54.833
big crystals.

13:54.900 --> 13:58.100
[ Breathes deeply ]

13:58.167 --> 13:59.544
Huh?

13:59.568 --> 14:00.967
Normal Diamondhead.

14:01.033 --> 14:01.933
Nice!

14:02.000 --> 14:03.000
[ Grunts ]

14:03.033 --> 14:04.100
So...

14:04.167 --> 14:05.894
do I just, like,

14:05.918 --> 14:07.667
sit here or what?

14:07.733 --> 14:10.800
[ Snoring ]

14:10.867 --> 14:12.333
[ Thunder crashes ]

14:12.400 --> 14:13.133
I'm awake!

14:13.200 --> 14:16.000
Oh, no, not again.

14:16.067 --> 14:17.494
I'm not even supercharged

14:17.518 --> 14:18.967
right now.

14:19.033 --> 14:20.133
[ Thunder crashing ]

14:20.200 --> 14:21.633
What's going on?

14:21.700 --> 14:23.367
Ben, are you doing this?

14:23.433 --> 14:24.777
Uh, I don't know.

14:24.801 --> 14:26.167
[ Grunts ]

14:29.067 --> 14:30.867
Everyone, get inside!

14:30.933 --> 14:33.933
[ Panting ]

14:35.467 --> 14:36.567
Is everyone okay?

14:36.633 --> 14:37.960
[ Beeping ]

14:37.984 --> 14:39.333
Huh? The lightning.

14:41.900 --> 14:43.300
Same as before.

14:43.367 --> 14:45.210
- Disappeared - as soon as you timed out.

14:45.300 --> 14:46.844
- How do you feel? - Ben?

14:46.933 --> 14:48.167
Stay away from me!

14:48.233 --> 14:50.067
Whoa. It's okay.

14:50.133 --> 14:51.443
- We'll figure this out - together.

14:51.467 --> 14:52.977
- I really - could've hurt you guys.

14:53.067 --> 14:54.533
I can't control this.

14:54.600 --> 14:56.377
- Vilgax: - You finally understand.

14:56.467 --> 14:57.494
If you do not yield

14:57.518 --> 14:58.567
the Omnitrix,

14:58.633 --> 15:00.944
catastrophe will visit

15:00.968 --> 15:03.300
both you and your loved ones.

15:03.367 --> 15:04.267
No!

15:04.333 --> 15:05.776
- This is Vilgax - we're talking about.

15:05.800 --> 15:07.677
It's getting worse.

15:07.701 --> 15:09.600
I have to do this.

15:09.667 --> 15:11.277
- Grandpa. - I know.

15:11.367 --> 15:12.667
This doesn't feel right.

15:12.733 --> 15:15.077
Surrender the Omnitrix quickly

15:15.101 --> 15:17.467
and we can end this.

15:17.533 --> 15:18.533
Okay, okay.

15:18.600 --> 15:20.444
- I just need a second - to say goodbye.

15:20.533 --> 15:22.133
[ Groans ]

15:22.200 --> 15:23.667
Goodbye, Four Arms.

15:23.733 --> 15:25.877
I'm gonna miss having

15:25.901 --> 15:28.067
four really big, beefy arms.

15:28.133 --> 15:29.467
[ Sniffles ]

15:29.533 --> 15:30.967
Goodbye, XLR8.

15:31.033 --> 15:32.267
I'm gonna miss...

15:32.333 --> 15:33.444
accelerating!

15:33.468 --> 15:34.600
[ Groans ]

15:34.667 --> 15:36.461
How is he just gonna give

15:36.485 --> 15:38.300
the Omnitrix to Vilgax?

15:38.367 --> 15:39.676
- Did he forget - it's attached to his arm?

15:39.700 --> 15:41.327
Oh, no. Grandpa,

15:41.351 --> 15:43.000
Ben's gonna lose his arm!

15:43.067 --> 15:44.433
He's not gonna lose his arm,

15:44.500 --> 15:45.527
because we're gonna

15:45.551 --> 15:46.600
put a stop to this.

15:46.667 --> 15:47.911
[ Thunder crashes ]

15:47.935 --> 15:49.200
That's strange.

15:49.267 --> 15:50.311
Ben's not even using

15:50.335 --> 15:51.400
the Omnitrix right now.

15:51.467 --> 15:54.733
[ Evil laughter in distance ]

15:54.800 --> 15:56.011
Make sure the spirit walkers

15:56.035 --> 15:57.267
stay safe.

15:57.333 --> 15:59.044
- Gwen! - I'll be right back.

15:59.133 --> 16:00.677
- [ Thunder crashes ] - Whoa!

16:00.767 --> 16:02.044
Hail-O: Why would you initiate

16:02.068 --> 16:03.367
the lightning

16:03.433 --> 16:04.460
at such a crucial moment?

16:04.484 --> 16:05.533
[ Gasps ]

16:05.600 --> 16:07.544
This is unfortunate.

16:07.568 --> 16:09.533
Whoops.

16:09.600 --> 16:10.867
Quite.

16:10.933 --> 16:12.244
Ben:

16:12.268 --> 16:13.600
And goodbye, new guy.

16:13.667 --> 16:14.827
I was gonna call you

16:14.851 --> 16:16.033
Shock Rock,

16:16.100 --> 16:17.611
because you shock

16:17.635 --> 16:19.167
and you rock.

16:19.233 --> 16:20.610
- Enough! - [ Thunder crashes ]

16:20.700 --> 16:22.761
Hurry, boy, before it's too late

16:22.785 --> 16:24.867
to give me the Omnitrix!

16:24.933 --> 16:27.867
Well, I guess it's ti...

16:27.933 --> 16:28.994
Stop!

16:29.018 --> 16:30.100
It was the Weatherheads!

16:30.167 --> 16:32.133
They're working with Vilgax!

16:32.200 --> 16:33.544
Hail-O:

16:33.568 --> 16:34.933
We're not working for Vilgax.

16:35.000 --> 16:37.300
We are here on... vacation.

16:37.367 --> 16:38.794
Hand over the Omnitrix

16:38.818 --> 16:40.267
as planned.

16:40.333 --> 16:42.333
Gwen, get inside.

16:42.400 --> 16:44.344
- It is definitely - a coincidence

16:44.433 --> 16:45.677
That we are here

16:45.701 --> 16:46.967
at this exact moment.

16:47.033 --> 16:48.333
The Weatherheads?

16:48.400 --> 16:49.877
So the snow, the tornadoes,

16:49.901 --> 16:51.400
it wasn't me.

16:51.467 --> 16:53.100
It was all a trick.

16:53.167 --> 16:54.611
That means

16:54.635 --> 16:56.100
I was right about Vilgax!

16:56.167 --> 16:58.733
You wretched little brat!

16:58.800 --> 16:59.567
[ Grunts ]

16:59.633 --> 17:02.400
You sneaky, sneaky alien jerk!

17:02.467 --> 17:04.167
Playing tricks on kids?

17:04.233 --> 17:05.260
I am through

17:05.284 --> 17:06.333
with this charade.

17:06.400 --> 17:07.377
The Omnitrix

17:07.401 --> 17:08.401
is far more powerful

17:08.467 --> 17:09.933
than you can comprehend!

17:10.000 --> 17:12.127
And you are just a reckless

17:12.151 --> 17:14.300
child who will endanger himself

17:14.367 --> 17:16.094
and everything around him

17:16.118 --> 17:17.867
to play at being a hero!

17:17.933 --> 17:19.710
Maybe it is dangerous,

17:19.734 --> 17:21.533
but I believe in myself

17:21.600 --> 17:23.061
way more

17:23.085 --> 17:24.567
than I believe in you.

17:24.633 --> 17:27.633
♪♪♪

17:30.867 --> 17:31.961
If you want the Omnitrix,

17:31.985 --> 17:33.100
Vilgax,

17:33.167 --> 17:35.167
then come take it from me.

17:35.233 --> 17:37.400
With pleasure.

17:37.467 --> 17:39.010
- Oh, wait, wait, wait, - time out.

17:39.100 --> 17:40.244
I don't know my moves yet.

17:40.268 --> 17:41.433
Uh, hold on.

17:41.500 --> 17:43.277
- J.K. - [ Laughs ]

17:43.367 --> 17:44.961
I just remembered one.

17:44.985 --> 17:46.600
Go, Bluemerang!

17:46.667 --> 17:48.894
Pitiful. You still rely solely

17:48.918 --> 17:51.167
on... What? Aah!

17:51.233 --> 17:52.577
Oh, yeah!

17:52.601 --> 17:53.967
It does come back!

17:54.033 --> 17:56.133
[ Grunting ]

17:56.200 --> 17:58.933
Aah!

17:59.000 --> 18:00.677
Uh...

18:00.701 --> 18:02.400
Aah!

18:02.467 --> 18:04.867
Shield, shield, shield!

18:04.933 --> 18:06.760
Solid! A power boost!

18:06.784 --> 18:08.633
Uh-oh, too much power!

18:08.700 --> 18:10.500
Aah!

18:12.100 --> 18:13.767
[ Groans ]

18:16.633 --> 18:17.627
The boy's new alien

18:17.651 --> 18:18.667
is powerful.

18:18.733 --> 18:19.794
I fear

18:19.818 --> 18:20.900
that master Vilgax alone

18:20.967 --> 18:22.094
may not be enough to face

18:22.118 --> 18:23.267
this challenge.

18:23.333 --> 18:25.433
I mean I feel, not fear.

18:25.500 --> 18:27.700
Uh, I do not feel.

18:27.767 --> 18:29.427
Initiate

18:29.451 --> 18:31.133
the transformation sequence.

18:31.200 --> 18:34.333
♪♪♪

18:44.833 --> 18:46.744
Prepare yourselves

18:46.768 --> 18:48.700
for The Perfect Storm!

18:50.133 --> 18:51.677
Now is probably our best chance

18:51.701 --> 18:53.267
to get everyone out of here.

18:53.333 --> 18:56.100
This way, quickly!

18:56.167 --> 18:58.000
Ben.

18:58.067 --> 19:01.367
Aah!

19:01.433 --> 19:02.644
The Weatherheads?

19:02.668 --> 19:03.900
Oh, what happened?

19:03.967 --> 19:05.077
You couldn't afford

19:05.101 --> 19:06.233
three bodies anymore?

19:06.300 --> 19:08.394
Prepare yourselves

19:08.418 --> 19:10.533
for The Perfect Storm!

19:13.667 --> 19:15.500
Whoa!

19:15.567 --> 19:16.727
Oh, two against one?

19:16.751 --> 19:17.933
Typical.

19:18.000 --> 19:19.933
Fight faaaair!

19:20.000 --> 19:21.594
I will do whatever it takes,

19:21.618 --> 19:23.233
changeling.

19:23.300 --> 19:25.700
♪♪♪

19:25.767 --> 19:27.377
- Why are you working - with Vilgax?

19:27.467 --> 19:29.144
Vilgax promised us Earth

19:29.168 --> 19:30.867
in exchange for our services.

19:30.933 --> 19:32.294
And you believed him?

19:32.318 --> 19:33.700
Vilgax wants to...

19:33.767 --> 19:34.767
destroy Earth!

19:34.800 --> 19:35.961
He lied to me.

19:35.985 --> 19:37.167
He'll lie to you, too.

19:37.233 --> 19:40.333
That is a possibility.

19:40.400 --> 19:41.667
Do not look at me.

19:41.733 --> 19:43.160
I'm not the one

19:43.184 --> 19:44.633
who said trust Vilgax.

19:44.700 --> 19:46.811
That's right. Pay no attention

19:46.835 --> 19:48.967
to the alien energy power up!

19:49.033 --> 19:50.700
[ Grunts ]

19:52.700 --> 19:53.861
It's so good to be me

19:53.885 --> 19:55.067
right now.

19:55.133 --> 19:57.767
[ Grunting ]

19:57.833 --> 19:59.860
You don't deserve to wield

19:59.884 --> 20:01.933
the power of the Omnitrix!

20:03.800 --> 20:05.267
Whoa!

20:05.333 --> 20:07.060
You don't deserve eye lasers if

20:07.084 --> 20:08.833
you don't know how to use them.

20:08.900 --> 20:10.044
You only delay

20:10.068 --> 20:11.233
the inevitable.

20:11.300 --> 20:13.527
You will power down, and when

20:13.551 --> 20:15.800
you do, I will be unstoppable.

20:15.867 --> 20:17.811
Aah!

20:17.835 --> 20:19.800
What are you doing, you fools?

20:19.867 --> 20:21.344
You were never planning

20:21.368 --> 20:22.867
to give the Earth over to us.

20:22.933 --> 20:24.194
This is the definition

20:24.218 --> 20:25.500
of a betrayal,

20:25.567 --> 20:27.427
which would make us very,

20:27.451 --> 20:29.333
very angry if we...

20:29.400 --> 20:31.667
Actually, we are angry!

20:31.733 --> 20:33.127
We will take

20:33.151 --> 20:34.567
the Omnitrix for ourselves.

20:34.633 --> 20:36.410
The forecast today

20:36.434 --> 20:38.233
shows thunderstorms

20:38.300 --> 20:39.844
with a chance

20:39.868 --> 20:41.433
of ultimate destruction!

20:41.500 --> 20:44.533
Uh-oh. Yeah!

20:44.600 --> 20:45.644
What?!

20:45.668 --> 20:46.733
Stop, you fools!

20:46.800 --> 20:48.077
You will not trick us

20:48.101 --> 20:49.400
again!

20:49.467 --> 20:51.300
[ Grunting ]

20:51.367 --> 20:53.094
What's your forecast say

20:53.118 --> 20:54.867
about this?

20:54.933 --> 20:56.533
No! Aah!

20:56.600 --> 20:59.167
Miscalculation.

20:59.233 --> 21:00.900
Aah!

21:03.333 --> 21:04.467
[ Groans ]

21:04.533 --> 21:05.744
[ Beeping ]

21:05.768 --> 21:07.000
Ooh, just in time.

21:07.067 --> 21:09.100
That was intense.

21:09.167 --> 21:10.167
You did it, Ben.

21:10.200 --> 21:11.400
- Vilgax - and the Weatherheads

21:11.433 --> 21:12.977
- Won't be bothering us - for a while.

21:13.067 --> 21:14.227
Which will give you more time

21:14.251 --> 21:15.433
to master this new alien.

21:15.500 --> 21:17.544
Yeah, I can't believe Vilgax

21:17.568 --> 21:19.633
did all this for the Omnitrix.

21:19.700 --> 21:21.144
I can't believe you were

21:21.168 --> 21:22.633
actually gonna give it to him.

21:22.700 --> 21:24.044
Yeah, well,

21:24.068 --> 21:25.433
he had me all mixed up.

21:25.500 --> 21:26.961
The truth is I am making this up

21:26.985 --> 21:28.467
as I go along,

21:28.533 --> 21:30.200
and I don't want to mess up.

21:30.267 --> 21:31.633
Don't feel too bad, Ben.

21:31.700 --> 21:32.677
Those four had us

21:32.701 --> 21:33.701
all chasing our tails.

21:33.767 --> 21:35.344
In the end, I decided

21:35.368 --> 21:36.967
to listen to my guts!

21:37.033 --> 21:38.133
[ Grunts ]

21:38.200 --> 21:39.527
Well, it's good to question

21:39.551 --> 21:40.900
things sometimes.
